&quot;I take no responsibility whatsoever for those who get dizzy and pass out from running around this post.&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=superflat@polykarbonbbs>superflat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/16/02 8:09:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11649.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> I'm I chess player, or at least I used to be.<br>
<br>
I like what you've got so far but I think you still need to do some serious reworking of the gameplay because, as is, this really isn't going to fly.<br>
<br>
First off, the player in the center can't win.  Its just not possible under any realistic circumstances.  He/she is being attacked by both players each move, but can only react to one of them.  Effectively its like losing initiative (called tempo in chess jargon) each turn.  Its death.  I wouldn't be suprised if there was a version of fool's mate that would be guaranteed to suceed.<br>
<br>
Secondly, the pawns.  How do the white's Western pawns and black's Eastern pawns move?  Either way seems problematic.  If they have to move in the same direction as gray's Western and Eastern pawns, then they're pretty much totally useless (especially if they have to capture moving that direction).  If they go the other way then the endgame is going to be screwed up.  Once gray is out of the way and pieces have been traded off, people are going to try to promote pawns.  But now not only is the board way longer, but you have to punch through twice as many pawns to get to the backrow.  Its also unlikely that having that second row will be as helpful offensively because having pawns lined up like that is tactically weak.  Even setting that aside, if the backrow pawns can be used to support the front row, then what's going to happen is that both players are going to get hopelessly entrenched.  Remember, the way you break through strong pawn positions is to usually to use attacks with stronger pieces on the start of the pawn chain.  But now pawns outnumber pieces 2:1!<br>
<br>
So yeah, its a good idea, but I think the rules, or the board, need some tweaking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chocoking>ChocoKing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/16/02 9:32:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11649.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://chiyoko.homestead.com/files/yattasml.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> superflat: He already took care of that it looks like:<br>
